title: For Sale:  Extremely rare Star 31P
postcontent: Up for sale is a super rare, not one even for sale on any firearm website i can find right now, Star 31P. If you don't know much about them they are some of the highest quality handguns ever produced. It has a totally forged steel frame, slide and barrel. These are Spanish military handguns and it was actually in the competition to be the U.S. military's service handgun. It lost to the M9 only because of the weight (it's forged steel). But they are known to be built like tanks and will last many millenia!!! This one is a steal. Just the gun sells for about $500 when they come up AND it has three factory magazines, two stainless and one blue. The magazines themselves sell for a minimum of $75 each. This pistol has one or two small scratches but has been fired very minimally. I would say less than 50 times. It is near mint with a like new bore and chamber. It was manufactured in the late 1980s. It is basically a design cross between a Browning HiPower with a cammed barrel and a Sig 210 with internal rails which provide unbelievable stability. It also has a steel full length guide rod from the factory. The industry went alloy frame in the 1990s and polymer after that. This is quality equal to the finest pistols ever made from the 1930s to the 1980s. It is 15+1 also and has a decocker on the safety that is ambidextrous. Very rare opportunity on this one and there is a huge collector market for these pistols. It sold new for $575 when it was new.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Westernfield 565F 12ga pump
postcontent: Looking to sell a Westernfield 565F 12ga pump. Shotgun has a fair amount of wear on the outside, but no major rust or pitting. Bore is perfect. The barrel has been cut down to 18in and has no front bead sight. These were made by Nobel back in the 1960s for retail sales at Montgomery Wards. This is a Nobel Model 60 to be exact. I bought this for $100, but required about $50 in parts from Numrich to fix a couple broken and missing items. It shoots and ejects fine, but loading shells isn't as smooth as it should be. Has some sharp edging inside that is gripping the shells as they load. Anyone proficient with a set of files can deburr this to smooth it out. It also has a sticky shell block, meaning it sometimes loads a shell, sometimes not cause the shell block is stuck uipward in the way. Reason being was the factory one wasn't working doing anything in terms of stopping. When I pumped it it would dump all shells in the tube. So I bought a replacement from Numrich, but for a 16ga.
